summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 1167, entitled "An Ordinance empowering the Columbia and Puget Sound Railroad Company, its successors or its assigns, to erect, maintain and use a trestle and elevated roadway and railway along, upon and over King Street, crossing Railroad Avenue, Commercial Street, South Second Street, South Third Street, South Fourth Street, South Fifth Street, and the alleys between said streets, in the City of Seattle," approved July 27, 1889.
